The White House has announced the U.S. members of the U.S.-India CEO Forum, a mechanism for strengthening economic ties between the two countries. The CEO participants will discuss opportunities for new partnerships between businesses in the United States and India, promoting investment and job growth, and addressing the concerns of U.S. and Indian business leaders. The U.S. Members will serve two-year terms. The government co-chairs of the Forum are Mike Froman and Montek Singh Ahluwalia. Senior government officials are expected to be present at the Forum meeting, including Dr. Larry Summers, Tim Geithner, Gary Locke, Ron Kirk, and Robert Hormats.